solver.sharedMemory.combinedSolver.pipelined

Class MutExPipelinedScheduling

  • java.lang.Object
    • solver.Z3Context
      • solver.Z3Solver
        • solver.sharedMemory.combinedSolver.MutualExclusionSolver
          • solver.sharedMemory.combinedSolver.pipelined.MutExPipelinedScheduling
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BufferConstraints, LatencyConstraints, PeriodConstraints, ProcessorConstraints, SolverFunctions, PeriodProcConstraints

    public class MutExPipelinedScheduling
extends MutualExclusionSolver
implements PeriodProcConstraints, PeriodConstraints
    The pipelined problem is solved using this class by a Mutual exclusion solver. Different constraints that are used to solve this problem are explained in the Verimag report : "Strictly Periodic Scheduling of Acyclic Synchronous Dataflow Graphs using SMT Solvers" Verimag Research Report no TR-2014-5
    Author:
    Pranav Tendulkar
